      <section id="id1824818">
        <title>To resist name calling of any kind [LO 2.5.1]</title>
        <para id="id4284746">ROLE- PLAY</para>
        <para id="id6966205">1. Sometimes people label certain groups of people and call them names. People who like Boeremusiek, for example, are sometimes called “rock spiders”. There are many more examples. Is this fair? What do you think about labelling people like this?</para>
        <para id="id7125672">Split up into groups and plan a play. Although the play is about <emphasis effect="italics">N</emphasis><emphasis effect="italics">ame-calling,</emphasis> the message to the class must be that it is wrong to call people nasty names. You may use a true experience.</para>
      </section>
