      <section id="id2976208">
        <title>To understand words which imitate their sound [LO 3.2.3]</title>
        <para id="id3112777">1. Read the following poem aloud and listen carefully to the sounds of the words:</para>
        <para id="id4324316">The castanets</para>
        <section id="id4488509">
          <title>The swishing skirts</title>
          <para id="id4006017">The throbbing beat</para>
          <para id="id1560811">The tapping feet</para>
          <para id="id4265883">The moon so high</para>
          <para id="id3557486">The stars so bright</para>
          <para id="id7459107">The gypsies dance and sing tonight.</para>
          <para id="id2177505">Flamenco!</para>
          <figure id="id4128491">
            <media id="id4128491_media" alt="">
              <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics1-4174.png" id="id4128491__onlineimage" height="188" width="107"/>
            </media>
          </figure>
          <para id="id6441846">2. Look up the following words in your dictionary and, in your own words, write down what they mean:</para>
          <para id="id7014981">flamenco …………………………………………………………………………………</para>
          <para id="id2134157">castanets …………………………………………………………………………………</para>
          <para id="id7435316">swish …………………………………………………………………………………</para>
          <para id="id7117490">gypsy …………………………………………………………………………………</para>
          <para id="id3472178">3. In which country do you think this scene is set?</para>
          <para id="id6417431"> This scene is probably set in …………………………………………………………….</para>
          <para id="id3265991">4. Which words in the poem rhyme?</para>
          <para id="id4241824">a) ……………………….. rhymes with  ……………………………</para>
          <para id="id7315102">b) ……………………….. rhymes with  ……………………………</para>
          <para id="id3421815">5. Did you notice that the word “swishing” copies the sound made by the skirts? Find two more words – in the poem - that copy (imitate) sound.</para>
          <para id="id7054498"> a) ……………………….. imitates ……………………………</para>
          <list id="id1837673" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha" mark-suffix=")">
            <item>………………………. imitates …………………………….</item>
          </list>
          <para id="id7024318">6. Can you make up a word to imitate the sounds that the castanets might make?</para>
          <para id="id3649898">……………………………………………………………………………………..</para>
        </section>
      </section>
